tember 28, 2018|work=cagematch.net}}</ref>\n**[[List of Pro Wrestling Illustrated awards#Rookie of the Year|Rookie of the Year]] (2018)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwi-online.com/pages/PWIawards.html|title=Pro Wrestling Illustrated Awards|publisher=PWI-Online.com|accessdate=March 2, 2019}}</ref>\n*'''''[[Sports Illustrated]]'''''\n**Ranked No. 4 of the top 10 female wrestlers in 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://amp.si.com/wrestling/2018/12/28/wwe-wrestling-women-top-10-wrestlers-award|title=Week in Wrestling: Top 10 Women's Wrestlers of the Year|work=[[Sports Illustrated]]|first=Justin|last=Barrasso|date=December 28, 2018|accessdate=April 4, 2019}}</ref>\n* '''''[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter|Wrestling Observer Newsletter awards]]'''''\n** [[List of Wrestling Observer Newsletter awards#Rookie of the Year|Rookie of the Year]] (2018)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.postwrestling.com/2019/03/17/bonus-show-wrestling-observer-newsletter-awards/|title=BONUS SHOW: Wrestling Observer Newsletter Awards|date=March 17, 2019|accessdate=March 23, 2019|work=[[Live Audio Wrestling|Post Wrestling]]}}</ref>\n* '''[[WWE]]'''\n** [[WWE Raw Women's Championship]] ([[List of WWE Raw Women's Champions|1 time]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/titlehistory/raw-womens-championship|title=Raw Women's Championship|website=WWE|accessdate=June 5, 2019}}</ref>\n** [[Slammy Award]] for \"This is Awesome\" Moment of the Year ([[Slammy Award#2015 Slammy Awards|2015]]) \u2013 {{small|with [[Dwayne Johnson|The Rock]]}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/2015-12-21/2015-slammy-award-winners|title=2015 Slammy Award winners|date=December 16, 2015|accessdate=April 27, 2018|publisher=[[WWE]]}}</ref>\n** WWE Year\u2013End Award for Best Diss of the Year (2018)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/wwe-announces-year-end-awards-instagram-becky-lynch-braun-strowman/|title=WWE Announces Year-End Awards on Instagram|author=Jeremy Thomas|work=411Mania|date=December 23, 2018|accessdate=December 23, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Mixed martial arts record==\n{{MMArecordbox\n| draws=\n| nc=\n| ko-wins= 3\n| ko-losses= 2\n| sub-wins= 9\n| sub-losses= \n| dec-wins= \n| dec-losses= \n| dq-wins=\n| dq-losses=\n| other-wins=\n| other-losses=\n}}\n{{MMA record start}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|12\u20132\n|[[Amanda Nunes]]\n|TKO (punches)\n|[[UFC 207]]\n|{{dts|2016|December|30|format=mdy}}\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|0:48\n|[[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|{{small|For the [[UFC Women's Bantamweight Championship]].}}\n|-\n| {{no2}}Loss\n| align=center| 12\u20131\n| [[Holly Holm]]\n| KO (head kick and punches)\n| [[UFC 193]]\n| {{dts|2015|November|15|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 2\n| align=center| 0:59\n| [[Melbourne]], Australia\n| {{small|Lost the [[UFC Women's Bantamweight Championship]]. Fight of the Night.}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 12\u20130\n| [[Bethe Correia]]\n| KO (punch)\n| [[UFC 190]]\n| {{dts|2015|August|1|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:34\n| [[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil\n| {{small|Defended the [[UFC Women's Bantamweight Championship]]. Performance of the Night.}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 11\u20130\n| [[Cat Zingano]]\n| Submission (straight armbar)\n| [[UFC 184]]\n| {{dts|2015|February|28|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:14\n| [[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n| {{small|Defended the [[UFC Women's Bantamweight Championship]]. Performance of the Night.}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 10\u20130\n| [[Alexis Davis (fighter)|Alexis Davis]]\n| KO (punches)\n| [[UFC 175]]\n| {{dts|2014|July|5|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:16\n| [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n| {{small|Defended the [[List of UFC Champions#Women's Bantamweight Championship|UFC Women's Bantamweight Championship]]. Performance of the Night.}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 9\u20130\n| [[Sara McMann]]\n| TKO (knee to the body)\n| [[UFC 170]]\n| {{dts|2014|February|22|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 1:06\n| [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n| {{small|Defended the [[List of UFC Champions#Women's Bantamweight Championship|UFC Women's Bantamweight Championship]]. Performance of the Night.}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 8\u20130\n| [[Miesha Tate]]\n| Submission (armbar)\n| [[UFC 168]]\n| {{dts|2013|December|28|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 3\n| align=center| 0:58\n| [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n| {{small|Defended the [[List of UFC Champions#Women's Bantamweight Championship|UFC Women's Bantamweight Championship]]. Submission of the Night. Fight of the Night.}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 7\u20130\n| [[Liz Carmouche]]\n| Submission (armbar)\n| [[UFC 157]]\n| {{dts|2013|February|23|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 4:49\n| [[Anaheim, California]], United States\n| {{small|Defended the [[List of UFC Champions#Women's Bantamweight Championship|UFC Women's Bantamweight Championship]].}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 6\u20130\n| [[Sarah Kaufman (fighter)|Sarah Kaufman]]\n| Submission (armbar)\n| [[Strikeforce: Rousey vs. Kaufman]]\n| {{dts|2012|August|18|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:54\n| [[San Diego, California]], United States\n| {{small|Defended the [[Strikeforce Women's Bantamweight Championship]]; Later promoted to [[UFC champions#Women's Bantamweight Championship|UFC Women's Bantamweight Champion]].}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 5\u20130\n| [[Miesha Tate]]\n| Technical Submission (armbar)\n| [[Strikeforce: Tate vs. Rousey]]\n| {{dts|2012|March|3|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 4:27\n| [[Columbus, Ohio]], United States\n| {{small|Bantamweight debut. Won the [[Strikeforce Women's Bantamweight Championship]].}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 4\u20130\n| [[Julia Budd]]\n| Submission (armbar)\n| [[2011 in Strikeforce#Strikeforce Challengers: Britt vs. Sayers|Strikeforce Challengers: Britt vs. Sayers]]\n| {{dts|2011|November|18|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:39\n| [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 3\u20130\n| [[Sarah D'Alelio]]\n| Technical Submission (armbar)\n| [[2011 in Strikeforce#Strikeforce Challengers: Gurgel vs. Duarte|Strikeforce Challengers: Gurgel vs. Duarte]]\n| {{dts|2011|August|12|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:25\n| [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 2\u20130\n| [[Charmaine Tweet]]\n| Submission (armbar)\n| HKFC: School of Hard Knocks 12\n| {{dts|2011|June|17|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:49\n| [[Calgary, Alberta]], Canada\n| {{small|Catchweight (150 lbs) bout.}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 1\u20130\n| [[Ediane Gomes]]\n| Submission (armbar)\n| [[2011 in King of the Cage#KOTC: Turning Point|KOTC: Turning Point]]\n| {{dts|2011|March|27|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:25\n| [[Tarzana, California]], United States\n|\n{{end}}\n\n{{MMA amateur record box\n| draws=\n| nc=\n| ko-wins=\n| ko-losses=\n| sub-wins= 3\n| sub-losses=\n| dec-wins=\n| dec-losses=\n| dq-wins=\n| dq-losses=\n| other-wins=\n| other-losses=\n}}\n{{MMA record start}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 3\u20130\n| Taylor Stratford\n| Submission (armbar)\n| Tuff-N-Uff - Las Vegas vs. 10th Planet Riverside\n| {{dts|2011|January|7|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:24\n| [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 2\u20130\n| Autumn King\n| Submission (armbar)\n| Tuff-N-Uff - Future Stars of MMA\n| {{dts|2010|November|12|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:57\n| [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 1\u20130\n| Hayden Munoz\n| Submission (armbar)\n| CFL - Ground Zero\n| {{dts|2010|August|6|format=mdy}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 0:23\n| [[Oxnard, California]], United States\n|\n{{end}}\n\n==Judo Olympic Games record==\n\n{| class=\"wikitabl